---
import { ChevronRight, CircleCheckBig, Lightbulb } from "@lucide/astro";
---

<section
  class="py-20 px-2 sm:px-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-t-[60px] rounded-b-none border-t border-color box-shadow"
>
  <div
    class="max-w-[1290px] mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 items-stretch"
  >
    <div class="lg:col-span-6 h-full flex flex-col">
      <p class="font-medium text-3xl leading-9 tracking-[-0.75px] mb-2">
        Every organization should be performing regular Risk Assessments
      </p>
      <p class="text-2xl font-normal leading-8 mb-6 mt-2 tracking-[-0.6px]">
        Risk assessment is a baseline requirement for nearly every compliance framework,
        and it's the right way to run your business. Identifying, prioritizing, and managing
        risks helps you protect your assets, earn customer trust, and prepare for audits with confidence.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="lg:col-span-6 flex justify-center items-center h-full">
      <div
        class="w-full h-full bg-card rounded-xl text-center flex justify-center items-center"
      >
        <img
          src="/assets/risk-business.png"
          alt="Compliance illustration"
          class="w-auto max-h-[350px] object-contain rounded-xl"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-20 px-2 sm:px-6 pt-4 relative bg-card">
  <div
    class="max-w-[1290px] mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 items-stretch mt-30 bg-card"
  >
    <div class="lg:col-span-5 h-full flex flex-col justify-between">
      <p class="font-medium text-3xl leading-9 tracking-[-0.75px] mb-2">
        Risk Assessment
      </p>
      <p class="text-base font-normal leading-8 mb-6 tracking-[-0.6px]">
        Identifying risks can be challenging! We recommend using a system
        of categories to ensure you have identified relevant risks.
      </p>

      <p class="text-base font-normal leading-8 mb-6 tracking-[-0.6px]">
        Using categories to identify risks is a powerful way to ensure thorough
        coverage. At Openlane, we provide a structured framework that helps teams
        distinguish categories of risk, enabling a more-complete and thoughtful
        discovery process. For each risk category, discuss how it applies to your
        organization. Do you have a robust business continuity plan? Is your
        intellectual property protected? Are there vendor dependencies or market
        risks to consider?
      </p>
      <p class="text-base font-normal leading-8 mb-6 tracking-[-0.6px]">
        At a minimum, most compliance frameworks - and any solid security posture -
        requires regular vulnerability scans, secure code reviews, and annual
        penetration tests of your infrastructure. Gaps in these areas represent
        real risks to your security, confidentiality, and availability. Document
        your findings in the Risk Module, then map each risk to related controls,
        policies, and procedures. Use the Status field to track risks across their
        lifecycle, from identification to mitigation to acceptance, so nothing
        falls through the cracks.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="lg:col-span-7 flex justify-center items-center h-full">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="flex items-start border border-border rounded-lg p-4">
          <CircleCheckBig size={23} class="text-color-primary mt-1 mr-2" />
          <div class="flex flex-col">
            <p class="text-lg font-normal">Compliance and Regulatory</p>
            <p class="text-base font-normal">
              Data Privacy, Compliance with Federal, State, Country-Specific
              Laws
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start border border-border rounded-lg p-4">
          <CircleCheckBig size={23} class="text-color-primary mt-1 mr-2" />
          <div class="flex flex-col">
            <p class="text-lg font-normal">Data</p>
            <p class="text-base font-normal">Data location, storage, and destruction</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start border border-border rounded-lg p-4">
          <CircleCheckBig size={23} class="text-color-primary mt-1 mr-2" />
          <div class="flex flex-col">
            <p class="text-lg font-normal">Business Continuity & Crisis</p>
            <p class="text-base font-normal">
              Disaster recovery and business continuity planning
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start border border-border rounded-lg p-4">
          <CircleCheckBig size={23} class="text-color-primary mt-1 mr-2" />
          <div class="flex flex-col">
            <p class="text-lg font-normal">Vendor Risks</p>
            <p class="text-base font-normal">
              Third-party service provider risks
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start border border-border rounded-lg p-4">
          <CircleCheckBig size={23} class="text-color-primary mt-1 mr-2" />
          <div class="flex flex-col">
            <p class="text-lg font-normal">Legal Risks</p>
            <p class="text-base font-normal">
              Regulatory compliance and legal obligations
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start border border-border rounded-lg p-4">
          <CircleCheckBig size={23} class="text-color-primary mt-1 mr-2" />
          <div class="flex flex-col">
            <p class="text-lg font-normal">Industry-Specific</p>
            <p class="text-base font-normal">
              Risks relevant to your industry
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start border border-border rounded-lg p-4">
          <CircleCheckBig size={23} class="text-color-primary mt-1 mr-2" />
          <div class="flex flex-col">
            <p class="text-lg font-normal">Cyber Insurance</p>
            <p class="text-base font-normal">
              Coverage and liability protection
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
